RACE.RACE_TEXT: RETAMA PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TM PURNCESS was allowed to settled behind the pace, rallied and moved out to be four wide in upper stretch and powered to the front and drew off in the end. RB NASH BASH stalked the pace then rallied three wide to put a head in front in between calls then came up empty in late stretch. WMA GRAND FINALE vied for the lead while between rivals, was in a long drive and weakened in late stretch. WMA SMOKE SIGNAL vied for the early lead while three wide, was in a long drive and gave way. SAINT SILKIE AA vied for the lead from the inside, was used up then faltered. WMA BADGE raced five wide on the backstretch, was used up then gave way. This race was hand timed.
